reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great price on like-new google 3a xl
reviews.reviewText: This is the second Google Pixel 3a XL I have purchased from havearly.com thru Amazon. Loved my first one so much I bought a second for my wife.Both phones were in perfect, like-new condition and functioned like new. They came with Android 11 and are supposedly getting Android 12.Great experience all the way around! Highly recommend Havearly and Amazon refurbished.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 14, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Can't believe I bought this without reading the reviews. How can they keep selling this if it's literally not unlocked like the title says. The phone seems in good condition and all. But kinda worthless if you don't use Verizon.I even called Verizon and tried to see if they could unlock it, but they found it was technically already unlocked, but that's clearly not what the phone itself says. They recommended I return it and get my refund, which is what I'm going to do.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 17, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Quality like new Google Pixel 3a XL!
reviews.reviewText: This replacement Google Pixel 3aXL felt just like my new model right when I opened the box. The volume, battery life, screen was really like new. It was only a 3/8" very thin scratch which took me a while to find anything wrong with it.My son also bought his replacement Pixel from this same seller six months ago.Note: Originals worked but we cracked our cells and never wanted to show pictures with the screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 19, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars This phone was $125 :-)
reviews.reviewText: I accidently shattered my last phone from these guys and I absolutely loved that phone. It was $175 last time I got one, and this time it was $125. If you don't care about getting the 'latest, greatest' phone, these are pretty incredible. I never had a problem with my last one and its demise was totally my fault.. I think it would of lasted at least a couple of years. I love the big screen, pic quality, pretty much everything about it. I guess if I had to complain it would be that the finger reader wasn't able to read my print a lot of the times .. eventually, second/ third try it's fine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Product, Great Phone Wrong listing
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this phone for my daughter for Christmas. I have had pixels and love them. She wanted one as well. I purchased this phone as it was listed as an unlocked phone. It was not. I have AT&T the phone that we received was for Verizon. Plus the phone had a bad scratch on the glass front. I was very disappointed. The phone is great the listing by Amazon was completely incorrect. I have had better success with eBay.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 30, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not an UNLOCKED phone!!!
reviews.reviewText: The phone is locked to the Verizon network! My old phone died with 4 months of service left on my Mint mobile SIM, so four months of prepaid service down the drain. Instead of wasting precious time with Amazon/Verizon customer service, I switched to Visible and got the phone up and running within 15 minutes after receiving the SIM card.
